When it comes to making fried pork, this dish should be prepared in a delicate way or, otherwise, you end up with dry tough pork. Try by boiling first, adding in a squeeze of lemon juice can help tenderize the pork while it is boiling under medium heat. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 In a pan, heat the oil over medium heat. Step 2 In a bowl, combine the salt pepper and diced pork, then fry in the oil. Step 3 Add in garlic and onions after frying for 3 minutes, fry until golden brown. Step 4 Reduce the heat then add in blended tomatoes for that extra sauce. Cover and cook for 4 minutes Step 5 Combine well then remove from heat and serve hot Another way you can roast it instead.